to the editor re mayor favors plans to ease housing shortage news article aug 3 since 1993 monthly rents in new york city have increased hitting low  and middle income families the hardest new yorkers in 21 of the city 's 59 community districts spend more than 30 percent of their annual income on rent by federal standards even the least expensive rental housing in new york city is unaffordable for most poor families new housing construction tax abatements and housing subsidies top the list of ways to help families who want to live work and raise their children in new york city but while the city needs to develop a housing plan it also needs state and federal partners to help pay for it nancy locker new york aug 3 2000 the writer is president of the citizens committee for children of new york

